<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-09-22T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-09-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="826" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d826">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11 G 93/1190: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-22T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 22,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>12. Minister from Ecuador asked August 19th that Guayaquil and Quito
                            Railway matter be submitted to arbitration in accordance with Article 27
                            of the contract. In view of statements made in your despatch No. 701,
                            July 28, Department was hopeful prospects of amicable settlement would
                            make this unnecessary. Investigate and cable brief statement situation
                            with recommendations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
